CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 13, 1962, pg. A16, reads: "D.I. Associates - Working happily for the scintillating D.I. Club, whose Jan. 28 style show for MENDS (neuromuscular diseases) are these associate members: Mary Jean Eaton, Birdie Dunlap and Ida Jones. Between them is one of the Treasure Chests which will make some lucky patron very, very happy. -Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: D. I. Club members Mary Jean Eaton, Birdie Dunlap, and Ida Jones, gathered around treasure chest to be raffled off at the "Melody in Fashion" MENDS benefit at Holiday House, another version
